snippet: Indonesia granted the badminton player Misha Zilberman a visa to compete in the world championships in Jakarta after a standoff lasting months, Israel’s Olympic committee said.
lead_paragraph: Indonesia granted the badminton player Misha Zilberman a visa to compete in the world championships in Jakarta after a standoff lasting months, Israel’s Olympic committee said.

headline.main: Indonesia Relents on Visa for Israeli
